Parliament of Catalonia daily sessions

projectDesc.p: ParlaMint is a project that aims to (1) create a multilingual set of comparable corpora of parliamentary proceedings uniformly encoded according to the ParlaMint encoding guidelines, covering the period from 2015 to mid-2022; (2) add linguistic annotations to the corpora and machine-translate them to English; (3) make the corpora available through concordancers; and (4) build use cases in Political Sciences and Digital Humanities based on the corpus data.

prefixDef.p: Private URIs with this prefix point to aligned source elements of the MTed corpus.

div.head: Sessió 60.1
div.note: The session opens in the morning and three minutes. He chairs the Speaker of Parliament, accompanied by the First Vice-President and the Third and Fourth Secretaries. Attend the Bureau the secretary general, the major and the major Miquel Lluís Palomares Amat.

The President of the Government, accompanied by the Vice-President of the Government and Councillor of the Economy and History and the Councillors of the Presidency, of the Interior, of Education, of Health, of Territories and Sustainability, of Culture, of Treball, of Social Afers and Families, of Enterprise and Knowledge and of Agriculture, of Ramaderia, of Fisheries and Food.
ORDER OF THE DAY OF THE CONVENTION
1. Ask with an oral answer.

Two. Decree-Law 29/2020 of 28 July, on which presuppositionary measures are adopted in relation to the deployment of social welfare activities, the ordering and strengthening of certain social services of residential character and day care provided for by the Residence Contingency Plan, in order to deal with the outbreaks of the pandemic generated by the Covid-19, for which the effect of the pandemic generated by the Covid-19 is maintained in terms of infancy and adolescence of the Decree-Law 11/2020, of 7 April, for which economic, social and administrative measures are adopted to address the effects of the pandemic generated by the Covid-19 and other complementarities, and for which the Decree-Law 21/2020, of 2 June, of the Economic and Social Charter measures are amended. 203-00054/12). Government of the Generalitat. Discussion and vote on the validation or repeal of the law decree (text presented: BOPC 671, 23).

Three. Decree No. 30/2020, dated 4 August, establishing the specific sanctioning regime for failure to comply with health prevention and containment measures to cope with the health crisis caused by the Covid-19 (tram. 203-00055/12). Government of the Government Debate and vote on the validation or repeal of the law decree (text presented: BOPC 671, 31).

4. Proposition of the law of urgent measures in the matter of yield containment in leases of habitating (tram. 202-00080/12). Parliamentary Group of Junts for Catalonia, Parliamentary Group Republicà, Parliamentary Group of Catalonia in Comú May and Parliamentary Subgroup of the Popular Unity Candidate - Constituent Creed. Discussion and vote on the items presented in the single reading and the items submitted subsequent to the opinion of the Board of State Guarantees (text presented: BOPC 651, 27).

Five. Proposal to present to the Bureau of the Congress of Deputies the Law Proposal to guarantee the social return of the bank bailout (tram. 270-00002/12). Parliamentary Group Republic. Totality debate and vote on the whole (text presented: BOPC 472, 164).
Six. Inquiries to the Government on education and the planning of the 2020-21 school year (tram. 300-00291/12). Socialist Parliamentary Group and Units for Progress. Substance.
7. Interview with the Government on the school year 2020-2021 (tram. 300-00292/12). Parliamentary Group of Ciutadans. Substance.
Eight. Interview with the Government on the school year 2020-2021 (tram. 300-00295/12). Parliamentary Subgroup of the Popular Unity Candidate - Constituent Creed. Substance.
Nine. Interview with the Government on the occupation and socio-occupational conditions of self-employment (tram. 300-00293/12). Parliamentary Group of Ciutadans. Substance.
Ten. Question to the Government on the regularization of immigrants (tram. 300-00296/12). Parliamentary Group Republic. Substance.
11. He asked the Government about the need for a rescue plan for the cultural sector (tram. 300-00294/12). Concepción Abellán Carretero, del Grup Parlamentari de Catalunya en Comú Puem. Substance.
12. Question to the Government on the defence of institutions and self-government (tram. 300-00298/12). Joint Parliamentary Group for Catalonia. Substance.
13. Question to the Government on the productive economy (tram. 300-00299/12). Joint Parliamentary Group for Catalonia. Substance.
14. He asked the Government about the management of the Covid-19 funds for economic and social recovery (tram. 300-00297/12). Parliamentary Group Republic. Substance.
15. Motion subsequent to the Government's inquiry into the Government's presuppositional policy (tram. 302-00228/12). Parliamentary Group of Ciutadans. Debate and vote.
16. Motion subsequent to the Government's inquiry into economic management (tram. 302-00232/12). Socialist Parliamentary Group and Units for Progress. Debate and vote.

17. Motion subsequent to the Government's inquiry into the misinformation and lack of transparency in the Government's external action (tram. 302-0029/12). Parliamentary Group of Ciutadans. Debate and vote.
18. Following the question to the Government on the balance of the general policy of the Government (tram. 302-00230/12). Parliamentary Subgroup of the People's Party of Catalonia. Debate and vote.
19. Motion subsequent to the Government's inquiry into Lleida's confinement and lower Segrià (promenade. 302-00231/12). Socialist Parliamentary Group and Units for Progress. Debate and vote.
Twenty. Motion subsequent to the Government's inquiry into industrial policy (tram. 302-00233/12). Grupo Parlamentari de Catalunya en Comú Pueder. Debate and vote.
The President
